Platinum’s efforts to create an inclusive and supportive work culture have resulted in excellent retention rates.  For example, the average investment management industry experience of our fund managers was 18.8 years (as at 11 May 2016), with an average of 14.2 years at Platinum.  The average number of years with Platinum for the remainder of the investment team was more than five years.  The average number of years at Platinum for non-investment team staff was nearly seven years.  Moreover, it is not uncommon to find departed employees re-join Platinum after spending several years in other countries or industries.
Making a Contribution to the Financial Advisory Industry
At Platinum, we believe that being a member of the financial services industry entails a duty to help improve the industry.
Financial Reform
Financial advisers play an important part in Australia’s financial services system.  The government has essentially forced the public through savings/superannuation schemes to rely on intermediaries to secure their long-term financial well-being.  However, there is confusion in our legislation as to the obligations of independence of financial advice.
In early 2014, we took the opportunity of the Future of Financial Advice (FoFA) reform bill and made a submission to the Senate inquiry on this important issue.  We pointed out the huge concentration of power in the hands of the country’s four big banks and the detriments their considerable influence over financial advisers can bring to the investing public.  In highlighting the lack of protection investors face regarding the efficacy of advice obtained from financial intermediaries, we urged the lawmakers to give more consideration to the interest of the public in the FoFA reform.
Education
To play a small part in raising the professionalism in the financial advisory industry, Platinum together with the Neilson Foundation are funding a total of 20 scholarships a year at five Australian universities, each scholarship being to the value of $15,000 per year11. The scholarships are to be awarded to students who are majoring in financial planning. 40% of the scholarships awarded since the programme began in 2014 have been awarded to female students. Platinum has further committed to providing valuable work experience opportunities for two candidates from this programme each year.
Commitment to Climate Action
We are committed to operating our business in an environmentally responsible and sustainable manner. Platinum continues its long-standing commitment to combating climate change with the measurement and offsetting of its carbon footprint.



[1] “Funds under management (FUM)”, i.e. the amount of money that we manage, is the key variable for Platinum’s business model and an important determinant of our profit.  FUM is significantly influenced by performance of our individual funds and investment mandates.  Click on the “Funds Under Management” tab on our Shareholder Information page to see the history of FUM.  Click here to see the latest FUM data for each of the funds managed by Platinum.



